\title{Invoice Organizer}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Automatically organizes invoices and receipts for tax preparation by}

\subtree{
\title{Invoice Organizer}
\p{This skill transforms chaotic folders of invoices, receipts, and financial documents into a clean, tax-ready filing system without manual effort.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\ul{
\li{Preparing for tax season and need organized records}
\li{Managing business expenses across multiple vendors}
\li{Organizing receipts from a messy folder or email downloads}
\li{Setting up automated invoice filing for ongoing bookkeeping}
\li{Archiving financial records by year or category}
\li{Reconciling expenses for reimbursement}
\li{Preparing documentation for accountants}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{What This Skill Does}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Reads Invoice Content}: Extracts information from PDFs, images, and documents:}
\li{Vendor/company name}
\li{Invoice number}
\li{Date}
\li{Amount}
\li{Product or service description}
\li{Payment method}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Renames Files Consistently}: Creates standardized filenames:}
\li{Format: \code{\startverb YYYY-MM-DD Vendor - Invoice - ProductOrService.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{Examples: \code{\startverb 2024-03-15 Adobe - Invoice - Creative Cloud.pdf\stopverb}}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Organizes by Category}: Sorts into logical folders:}
\li{By vendor}
\li{By expense category (software, office, travel, etc.)}
\li{By time period (year, quarter, month)}
\li{By tax category (deductible, personal, etc.)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Handles Multiple Formats}: Works with:}
\li{PDF invoices}
\li{Scanned receipts (JPG, PNG)}
\li{Email attachments}
\li{Screenshots}
\li{Bank statements}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Maintains Originals}: Preserves original files while organizing copies}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{How to Use}
\subtree{
\title{Basic Usage}
\p{Navigate to your messy invoice folder:}

\pre{\startverb
cd ~/Desktop/receipts-to-sort
\stopverb}

\p{Then ask Claude Code:}

\pre{\startverb
Organize these invoices for taxes
\stopverb}

\p{Or more specifically:}

\pre{\startverb
Read all invoices in this folder, rename them to 
"YYYY-MM-DD Vendor - Invoice - Product.pdf" format, 
and organize them by vendor
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Advanced Organization}
\pre{\startverb
Organize these invoices:
1. Extract date, vendor, and description from each file
2. Rename to standard format
3. Sort into folders by expense category (Software, Office, Travel, etc.)
4. Create a CSV spreadsheet with all invoice details for my accountant
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Instructions}
\p{When a user requests invoice organization:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Scan the Folder}}
\li{Total number of files}
\li{File types}
\li{Date range (if discernible from names)}
\li{Current organization (or lack thereof)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Extract Information from Each File}}
\li{Use text extraction to read invoice content}
\li{Look for common patterns:}
\li{"Invoice Date:", "Date:", "Issued:"}
\li{"Invoice #:", "Invoice Number:"}
\li{Company name (usually at top)}
\li{"Amount Due:", "Total:", "Amount:"}
\li{"Description:", "Service:", "Product:"}
\li{Read visible text from images}
\li{Identify vendor name (often at top)}
\li{Look for date (common formats)}
\li{Find total amount}
\li{Use filename clues}
\li{Check file creation/modification date}
\li{Flag for manual review if critical info missing}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Determine Organization Strategy}}
\li{\strong{By Vendor} (Adobe/, Amazon/, Stripe/, etc.)}
\li{\strong{By Category} (Software/, Office Supplies/, Travel/, etc.)}
\li{\strong{By Date} (2024/Q1/, 2024/Q2/, etc.)}
\li{\strong{By Tax Category} (Deductible/, Personal/, etc.)}
\li{\strong{Custom} (describe your structure)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Create Standardized Filename}}
\li{\code{\startverb 2024-03-15 Adobe - Invoice - Creative Cloud.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb 2024-01-10 Amazon - Receipt - Office Supplies.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb 2023-12-01 Stripe - Invoice - Monthly Payment Processing.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{Remove special characters except hyphens}
\li{Capitalize vendor names properly}
\li{Keep descriptions concise but meaningful}
\li{Use consistent date format (YYYY-MM-DD) for sorting}
\li{Preserve original file extension}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Execute Organization}}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Generate Summary Report}}
\li{Importing into accounting software}
\li{Sharing with accountants}
\li{Expense tracking and reporting}
\li{Tax preparation}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Provide Completion Summary}}
\li{\strong{Processed}: [X] invoices}
\li{\strong{Date range}: [earliest] to [latest]}
\li{\strong{Total amount}: $[sum] (if amounts extracted)}
\li{\strong{Vendors}: [Y] unique vendors}
\li{\code{\startverb /Invoices/\stopverb} - Organized invoices}
\li{\code{\startverb /Invoices/invoice-summary.csv\stopverb} - Spreadsheet for accounting}
\li{\code{\startverb /Invoices/originals/\stopverb} - Original files (if copied)}
\li{Review the \code{\startverb invoice-summary.csv\stopverb} file}
\li{Check files in "Needs Review" folder}
\li{Import CSV into your accounting software}
\li{Set up auto-organization for future invoices}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Examples}
\subtree{
\title{Example 1: Tax Preparation (From Martin Merschroth)}
\p{\strong{User}: "I have a messy folder of invoices for taxes. Sort them and rename properly."}

\p{\strong{Process}:}

\ol{
\li{Scans folder: finds 147 PDFs and images}
\li{Reads each invoice to extract:}
\li{Date}
\li{Vendor name}
\li{Invoice number}
\li{Product/service description}
\li{Renames all files: \code{\startverb YYYY-MM-DD Vendor - Invoice - Product.pdf\stopverb}}
\li{Organizes into: \code{\startverb 2024/Software/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb 2024/Travel/\stopverb}, etc.}
\li{Creates \code{\startverb invoice-summary.csv\stopverb} for accountant}
\li{Result: Tax-ready organized invoices in minutes}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 2: Monthly Expense Reconciliation}
\p{\strong{User}: "Organize my business receipts from last month by category."}

\p{\strong{Output}:}

\pre{\startverb
# March 2024 Receipts Organized

## By Category
- Software & Tools: $847.32 (12 invoices)
- Office Supplies: $234.18 (8 receipts)
- Travel & Meals: $1,456.90 (15 receipts)
- Professional Services: $2,500.00 (3 invoices)

Total: $5,038.40

All receipts renamed and filed in:
`Business-Receipts/2024/03-March/[Category]/`

CSV export: `march-2024-expenses.csv`
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 3: Multi-Year Archive}
\p{\strong{User}: "I have 3 years of random invoices. Organize them by year, then by vendor."}

\p{\strong{Output}: Creates structure:}

\pre{\startverb
Invoices/
├── 2022/
│   ├── Adobe/
│   ├── Amazon/
│   └── ...
├── 2023/
│   ├── Adobe/
│   ├── Amazon/
│   └── ...
└── 2024/
    ├── Adobe/
    ├── Amazon/
    └── ...
\stopverb}

\p{Each file properly renamed with date and description.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 4: Email Downloads Cleanup}
\p{\strong{User}: "I download invoices from Gmail. They're all named 'invoice.pdf', 'invoice(1).pdf', etc. Fix this mess."}

\p{\strong{Output}:}

\pre{\startverb
Found 89 files all named "invoice*.pdf"

Reading each file to extract real information...

Renamed examples:
- invoice.pdf → 2024-03-15 Shopify - Invoice - Monthly Subscription.pdf
- invoice(1).pdf → 2024-03-14 Google - Invoice - Workspace.pdf
- invoice(2).pdf → 2024-03-10 Netlify - Invoice - Pro Plan.pdf

All files renamed and organized by vendor.
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Organization Patterns}
\subtree{
\title{By Vendor (Simple)}
\pre{\startverb
Invoices/
├── Adobe/
├── Amazon/
├── Google/
└── Microsoft/
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{By Year and Category (Tax-Friendly)}
\pre{\startverb
Invoices/
├── 2023/
│   ├── Software/
│   ├── Hardware/
│   ├── Services/
│   └── Travel/
└── 2024/
    └── ...
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{By Quarter (Detailed Tracking)}
\pre{\startverb
Invoices/
├── 2024/
│   ├── Q1/
│   │   ├── Software/
│   │   ├── Office/
│   │   └── Travel/
│   └── Q2/
│       └── ...
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{By Tax Category (Accountant-Ready)}
\pre{\startverb
Invoices/
├── Deductible/
│   ├── Software/
│   ├── Office/
│   └── Professional-Services/
├── Partially-Deductible/
│   └── Meals-Travel/
└── Personal/
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Automation Setup}
\p{For ongoing organization:}

\pre{\startverb
Create a script that watches my ~/Downloads/invoices folder 
and auto-organizes any new invoice files using our standard 
naming and folder structure.
\stopverb}

\p{This creates a persistent solution that organizes invoices as they arrive.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pro Tips}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Scan emails to PDF}: Use Preview or similar to save email invoices as PDFs first}
\li{\strong{Consistent downloads}: Save all invoices to one folder for batch processing}
\li{\strong{Monthly routine}: Organize invoices monthly, not annually}
\li{\strong{Backup originals}: Keep original files before reorganizing}
\li{\strong{Include amounts in CSV}: Useful for budget tracking}
\li{\strong{Tag by deductibility}: Note which expenses are tax-deductible}
\li{\strong{Keep receipts 7 years}: Standard audit period}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Handling Special Cases}
\subtree{
\title{Missing Information}
\p{If date/vendor can't be extracted:}

\ul{
\li{Flag file for manual review}
\li{Use file modification date as fallback}
\li{Create "Needs-Review/" folder}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Duplicate Invoices}
\p{If same invoice appears multiple times:}

\ul{
\li{Compare file hashes}
\li{Keep highest quality version}
\li{Note duplicates in summary}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Multi-Page Invoices}
\p{For invoices split across files:}

\ul{
\li{Merge PDFs if needed}
\li{Use consistent naming for parts}
\li{Note in CSV if invoice is split}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Non-Standard Formats}
\p{For unusual receipt formats:}

\ul{
\li{Extract what's possible}
\li{Standardize what you can}
\li{Flag for review if critical info missing}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Related Use Cases}
\ul{
\li{Creating expense reports for reimbursement}
\li{Organizing bank statements}
\li{Managing vendor contracts}
\li{Archiving old financial records}
\li{Preparing for audits}
\li{Tracking subscription costs over time}
}
}
}